@Rythyrix: Those platform exclusive services are even worse then clearnet ones :P

---
As for security, most people will always take "the path of least resistance". In order to overcome that tendency, people have to find the value of protecting their privacy. But that won't happen until they actually feel threatened, and despite the numerous hacks and leaks, that still hasn't reached a breaking point yet.

@Plasmmer: ZeroMux isn't it's own site yet. It's a tool and libraries that help you generate a Dropbox like zite, and make pages that stream video. A properly made zite will have all those files marked optional so that they only download when you choose to download or stream them. Here's a [test site I made](http://127.0.0.1:43110/1FyYahC8sKVYfsPQXEzuRjXNDQeb6Y2xno/), the streaming page is linked on the left. Keep in mind that video streaming only works properly in Firefox currently due to an old bug in Chrome that hasn't been fixed due to it not being a problem until now.  

---
You can get and learn more about ZeroMux [here](http://127.0.0.1:43110/1CiDoBP8RiWziqiBGEd8tQMy66A6fmnw2V/big/docs/)
